Helping students at Bosco Jomo who don’t usually get a chance to learn has taught me the value of giving time to others. I go once a week for an hour and a half, and during that time, we not only study, but they share how hard it is to live away from their parents. I started this this year, and it has inspired me to pursue higher education and one day create ICT programs for students without resources. To make learning fun, I create small games and read long essays with them, which keeps us motivated. After tutoring, we play basketball, and I enjoy organizing zone games where everyone tries different positions, learning patience and teamwork. My spiritual school and community support inspire me to do all this with care and love.
